The paper deals with the complexity of solving Integer Programming (IP) problems, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and optimization. The paper uses techniques from computational complexity theory, graph theory, and linear algebra. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also discusses the branch-width and path-width of column-matroids, which are topics in graph theory, so cs.GT (Graph Theory) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper uses results from linear programming and optimization, which are related to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
